# REMOVED: 89fd4ba. It was listed here as "formatting-only" and it is NOT. Its message
# says "second Prettier pass" (3 spec files), but a `git add -A` also swept in 384
# untracked files that were sitting in the working tree — 376 third-party skill files
# under .agents/skills/design/, .mcp.json, and 7 Supabase CLI scratch files. The real
# commit is 388 files / 68,913 insertions.
#
# Ignoring it would have made `git blame` skip a commit that introduced 68k lines of
# real content — exactly the failure this file's header warns about. The lesson is in
# the header for a reason: verify a commit is formatting-only before listing it, and
# stage formatting passes with explicit paths, never `git add -A`.

